com.microsoft.identity.client

Interface AuthenticationCallback


  • public interface AuthenticationCallback
    Callback to use with token request. Authentication result or error will be returned back via callback.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void onCancel()
      Will be called if user cancels the flow.
      void onError(MsalException exception)
      Error occurs during the authentication.
      void onSuccess(AuthenticationResult authenticationResult)
      Authentication finishes successfully, AuthenticationResult will be sent back via the onSuccess.

    • Method Detail

      • onSuccess

        void onSuccess(AuthenticationResult authenticationResult)
        Authentication finishes successfully, AuthenticationResult will be sent back via the onSuccess.
        Parameters:
        authenticationResult - AuthenticationResult that contains the success response.

      • onError

        void onError(MsalException exception)
        Error occurs during the authentication.
        Parameters:
        exception - The MsalException contains the error code, error message and cause if applicable. The exception returned in the callback could be MsalClientException, MsalServiceException or MsalUiRequiredException.

      • onCancel

        void onCancel()
        Will be called if user cancels the flow.
